meanings.sent1: I will uncart the groceries from the shopping cart.
meanings.sent2: Please uncart the boxes from the delivery truck.
meanings.sent3: After the race, the exhausted runner had to uncart the heavy equipment.
meanings.sent4: She had to uncart the memories of her past to move forward.
meanings.sent5: The magician uncarted a rabbit from the top hat, surprising the audience.

meanings.definition: Not carted; not transported by cart.
meanings.sent1: The uncart items were left behind at the loading dock.
meanings.sent2: The uncart packages were scattered around the warehouse.
meanings.sent3: The uncart goods were forgotten and left to gather dust.
meanings.sent4: Her uncart luggage symbolized her spontaneous travel style.
meanings.sent5: The uncart boxes stood out among the neatly organized ones.
